 @valeriesurname  If you have used chatgpt or any other ai agents a lot, you would recognize the language. The step by step walkthrough, bullet point talking, no transitions between segments, very neutral choice of words, no personalized vocabulary, no pitch/tempo change just a constant yap session, very few non-verbal and facial communication. 
The fastest way to find out is if someone is talking like they are giving a presentation in middle school using a script they memorized or like a news reporter reading from a teleprompter(they sometimes do a good job of mixing emotions tho).
If you compare him with other youtubers like MKBHD, Doctor Mike, reallifelore, sillycorns you would immediately how soul less this video sounds.

 @BillearnDiecastCollection  Thanks for the reply and for sharing your Instagram. Funny thing, though, all I see are the same “hyped” models, most of them scalped to death. But hey, that’s your choice.

See, I’ve been collecting since 1998 — back when Hot Wheels even had that whole lead-paint controversy. For me (and a lot of genuine collectors), it was always about the fun of finding and enjoying affordable toys.

But nowadays, some folks hype up a few cars so much that they become impossible for actual collectors to get without paying ridiculous prices. Newsflash: these aren’t gold bars or retirement pensions, they’re die-cast cars. Not everything has to sit in a glass box like a stock portfolio.
